8 and on page 3, lines 31-32, by rewriting the lines to read:
9 "PART III. AMEND INTERIM APPOINTMENT CRITERIA FOR THE BUILDING
10 CODE COUNCIL AND RESIDENTIAL CODE COUNCIL
11 SECTION 3.(a) G.S. 143-136(a2) reads as rewritten:
12 "(a2) Process for Appointments by the Governor. – The Governor shall transmit to the
13 presiding officers of the Senate and the House of Representatives, within four weeks of the
14 convening of the session of the General Assembly in the year for which the terms in question are
15 initially appointed or are to expire, the names of the persons to be appointed by the Governor and
16 submitted to the General Assembly for confirmation by joint resolution. If an appointment is
17 required pursuant to this subsection when the General Assembly is not in session, the member
18 may be appointed and serve on an interim basis pending confirmation by the General Assembly.
19 For the purpose of this subsection, the General Assembly is not in session only (i) prior to
20 convening of the regular session, (ii) during any adjournment of the regular session for more than
21 10 90 days, or (iii) after sine die adjournment of the regular session."
22 SECTION 3.(b) G.S. 143-136.1(b1) reads as rewritten:
23 "(b1) Process for Appointments by the Governor. – The Governor shall transmit to the
24 presiding officers of the Senate and the House of Representatives, within four weeks of the
25 convening of the session of the General Assembly in the year for which the terms in question are
26 initially appointed or are to expire, the names of the persons to be appointed by the Governor and
27 submitted to the General Assembly for confirmation by joint resolution. If an appointment is
28 required pursuant to this subsection when the General Assembly is not in session, the member
29 may be appointed and serve on an interim basis pending confirmation by the General Assembly.
30 For the purpose of this subsection, the General Assembly is not in session only (i) prior to
31 convening of the regular session, (ii) during any adjournment of the regular session for more than
32 10 90 days, or (iii) after sine die adjournment of the regular session."
